# Keep USAGE.md up to date

[`USAGE.md`](USAGE.md) is the **authoritative** guide for forking the template, deployment, the component catalogue, and markup/JS examples. [`README.md`](README.md) stays sparse — link to USAGE.md; do not move long component docs back into README.

When you add or materially change a **reusable** feature, update USAGE.md in the same task (unless the user explicitly asks for docs-only or no-docs work).

## Update USAGE.md when you change

| Change | USAGE.md section |
| ------ | ---------------- |
| New `app/*.js` module or public API (`initX`, `showX`) | **Available features** table + **Using components** (markup + import example) |
| New CSS component pattern (`.foo`, BEM block) | **Available features** table + usage example if non-obvious |
| New `demo.html` section | Ensure **Using components** matches live demo; mention demo in feature row |
| Fork/deploy workflow (`pages.yml`, entry HTML) | **Creating a new app**, **GitHub Pages**, or **Project structure** |
| New optional asset path (`app/res/`, `vendor/`) | **Project structure** and/or fork checklist |

## Each component entry should include

1. One-line purpose in the **Available features** table
2. **Using components** subsection with:
   - Minimal HTML markup (classes, key `data-*` attributes)
   - `import` + `init` snippet
   - Notable options (data attributes, callbacks, `getSelected`/`setMode`, etc.)

Mirror existing entries (e.g. Dropdown, Toggle dropdown, Banners).

## Also update when relevant

- [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md) — module conventions table if a new `initX` / pattern is added
- [`demo.html`](demo.html) — interactive example for user-facing components
- Do **not** duplicate full usage into README; at most add a table row linking to USAGE.md

## Skip USAGE.md updates for

- Bug fixes with no API/markup change
- Internal refactors with no user-visible contract change
- App-specific logic in `main.js` on a fork (template `main.js` stays minimal)
